Pronounced with a long 'a' to distinguish from [[Hass]]. Often written ''Haße'', as would be correct following new German ortography (which is not introduced in Austria).
:''See also'' [[hasse]]
==German==
===Etymology===
From Viennese dialect ''hass'', "hot". Literally, "a hot one".
===Noun===
'''Hasse''' ''f''
